article.headline: Drexel 69, UNC Wilmington 55
article.story: PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Frank Elegar scored 20 points and three other Drexel players scored in double figures as the Dragons won their ninth straight game, 69-55 over North Carolina-Wilmington on Saturday. The Dragons (11-2, 3-0 Colonial Athletic Association) opened with a 16-2 run and never trailed. Drexel's winning streak is its longest since a nine-game run in 1996-97. Chaz Crawford finished with a game-high 15 rebounds and six blocks, and Dominick Mejia finished with 13 points. Scott Rodgers added 13 points and Bashir Mason chipped in with 12. Daniel Fountain scored 16 points and Vladimir Kuljanin added 15 for the Seahawks (0-3, 3-9), who shot just 33 percent and lost their fifth straight. North Carolina-Wilmington rallied within 39-33 with 13:45 left after Kuljanin made a layup. But Drexel regained control and Mejia hit a 3-pointer with 4:07 remaining to give the Dragons a 56-41 advantage. Crawford hit a layup with 6:54 left in the first half to give Drexel its biggest lead at 23-6. Drexel led 32-20 at halftime.
